      <div class="article-teaser">
        We are working with Croydon Council on transport plans to allow for growth expected in the A23/A232 Fiveways area. We hope to begin construction in late 2021 or early 2022.
        
      </div>
    
    
      <p>Since a 2017 consultation on our proposals, we have made changes to some areas of the design.</p>

<p>Our detailed response to that consultation, and final proposals showing how we want to move forward with the project, is on the <a href="https://consultations.tfl.gov.uk/roads/fiveways/?cid=fiveways-croydon">Fiveways Croydon consultation page</a>.</p>

<p>The finished work will help to support the <a href="/corporate/about-tfl/the-mayors-transport-strategy">Mayor's Transport Strategy</a>.</p>

<p>Overall the proposals aim to:</p>

<ul>
	<li>Improve road safety</li>
	<li>Create better conditions for pedestrians and cyclists</li>
	<li>Support growth in Croydon</li>
	<li>Improve journey times</li>
	<li>Create new public spaces to develop Waddon as a local centre</li>
</ul>
      
           
      
      
        
          
        
      
    
